        </doi_data>
        <citation_list><citation key="ref1"><unstructured_citation>arXiv, arxiv, 1803.02477, astro-ph, Intensity%20Mapping%20Cross-Correlations%20II:%20HI%20Halo%20Models%20Including%20Shot%20Noise, Intensity%20Mapping%20Cross-Correlations%20II, HI%20intensity%20mapping%20data%20traces%20the%20large-scale%20structure%20matter%20distribution%20using%20the%20integrated%20emission%20of%20neutral%20hydrogen%20gas%20(HI).%20The%20cross-correlation%20of%20the%20intensity%20maps%20with%20optical%20galaxy%20surveys%20can%20mitigate%20foreground%20and%20systematic%20effects,%20but%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20significantly%20depend%20on%20galaxy%20evolution%20parameters%20of%20the%20HI%20and%20the%20optical%20sample.%20Previously,%20we%20have%20shown%20that%20the%20shot%20noise%20of%20the%20cross-correlation%20scales%20with%20the%20HI%20content%20of%20the%20optical%20samples,%20such%20that%20the%20shot%20noise%20estimation%20infers%20the%20average%20HI%20masses%20of%20these%20samples.%20In%20this%20article,%20we%20present%20an%20adaptive%20framework%20for%20the%20cross-correlation%20of%20HI%20intensity%20maps%20with%20galaxy%20samples%20using%20our%20implementation%20of%20the%20halo%20model%20formalism%20(Murray%20et%20al%202018,%20in%20prep)%20which%20utilises%20the%20halo%20occupation%20distribution%20of%20galaxies%20to%20predict%20their%20power%20spectra.%20We%20compare%20two%20HI%20population%20models,%20tracing%20the%20spatial%20halo%20and%20the%20galaxy%20distribution%20respectively,%20and%20present%20their%20auto-%20and%20cross-power%20spectra%20with%20an%20associated%20galaxy%20sample.%20We%20find%20that%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20HI%20model%20and%20the%20distribution%20of%20the%20HI%20within%20the%20galaxy%20sample%20have%20minor%20significance%20for%20the%20shape%20of%20the%20auto-%20and%20cross-correlations,%20but%20highly%20impact%20the%20measured%20shot%20noise%20amplitude%20of%20the%20estimators,%20a%20finding%20we%20confirm%20with%20simulations.%20We%20demonstrate%20parameter%20estimation%20of%20the%20HI%20halo%20occupation%20models%20and%20advocate%20this%20framework%20for%20the%20interpretation%20of%20future%20experimental%20data,%20with%20the%20prospect%20of%20determining%20the%20HI%20masses%20of%20optical%20galaxy%20samples%20via%20the%20cross-correlation%20shot%20noise., ArXiv180302477%20Astro-Ph, Wolz,%20L.%20and%20Murray,%20S.%20G.%20and%20Blake,%20C.%20and%20Wyithe,%20J.%20S., mar, 2018, Astrophysics%20-%20Cosmology%20and%20Nongalactic%20Astrophysics, Comment:%2015%20pages,%208%20figures,%203%20tables.%20Comments%20welcome, 3</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref2"><unstructured_citation>New%20York, Dover%20Books%20on%20Physics, Statistical%20Fluid%20Mechanics, 1, Dover%20Publications, Monin,%20A.%20S.%20and%20Yaglom,%20A.%20M., 2007</unstructured_citation></citation><citation key="ref3"><doi>10.3847/1538-4357/aa7d0a</doi></citation><citation key="ref4"><doi>10.1111/j.1365-2966.2011.19250.x</doi></citation><citation key="ref5"><doi>10.1093/mnras/248.1.1</doi></citation><citation key="ref6"><doi>10.1017/CBO9780511804533.017</doi></citation><citation key="ref7"><unstructured_citation>Murray,%20S.%20G., powerbox:%20Make%20arbitrarily%20structured,%20atbitrary-dimension%20boxes%20and%20log-normal%20mocks, 2018, https://github.com/steven-murray/powerbox, 2018-07-23</unstructured_citation></citation></citation_list>
